== Spanish ==
===Etymology===
From French ''[[allemand]]'', from Latin ''[[alemannus]]'', from ancient High German ''[[alaman]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /aleˈman̪/
*[[SAMPA]]: /ale"man/

===Noun===

'''alemán''' {{m}} {{s}}, '''[[alemana]]''' {{f}} {{s}}, '''alemanes''' {{m}} {{p}}, '''alemanas''' {{f}} {{p}}
#[[German#Proper noun|German]] (inhabitant of [[Germany]] or person from German descent).
#:''Esta mañana llegaron unos '''alemanes''' a Bogotá.'' - This morning, some Germans arrived at [[w:Bogotá|Bogotá]].
#{{m}} German (language).
#:''Llevo dos años aprendiendo '''alemán'''.'' - I've been learning German for two years.

====Synonyms====
*(''person'') [[teutón]] (colloquial)
*(''language'') [[alto alemán]]

===Adjective===
'''alemán''' {{m}} {{s}}, '''[[alemana]]''' {{f}} {{s}}, '''alemanes''' {{m}} {{p}}, '''alemanas''' {{f}} {{p}}
#[[German#Adjective|German]] (relating to Germany or to the German language).
#:''Este [[carro]] '''alemán''' es [[rojo]].'' - This German [[car]] is [[red]].

====Synonyms====
*[[teutón]] (colloquial), [[germano]]

